Use the standard library
This is how to change_base of x and base:
   When x is 0, then:
      The answer is "0"
   End when
   Remember that digits is "0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ"
   Remember that result is ""
   Remember that n is x
   Do this 1000 times:
      When n is 0, then:
         Leave the loop
      End when
      Remember that r is remainder of n and base
      Remember that c is item r in digits
      Add c to result
      Remember that n is quotient of n and base
   End do
   The answer is reverse of result
Now you know
>>> change_base of 8 and 3
"22"
>>> change_base of 8 and 2
"1000"
>>> change_base of 7 and 2
"111"